		<description><![CDATA[Carmen Van Kerckhove makes issues of race her business. Van Kerckhove heads up New Demographic, a diversity education firm &#8220;dedicated to promoting relaxed, authentic, and productive conversations about race.&#8221;
Her work in the areas of race relations, racial identity, and diversity have lead to her appearance on CNN and MSNBC and, ultimately, to her acceptance to [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Carmen Van Kerckhove makes issues of race her business. Van Kerckhove heads up New Demographic, a diversity education firm &#8220;dedicated to promoting relaxed, authentic, and productive conversations about race.&#8221;</p>
<p>Her work in the areas of race relations, racial identity, and diversity have lead to her appearance on <a class="zem_slink" title="CNN" rel="homepage" href="http://www.cnn.com/">CNN</a> and <a class="zem_slink" title="MSNBC" rel="homepage" href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/">MSNBC</a> and, ultimately, to her acceptance to the Malan race.</p>
<p>Van Kerckhove is not only familiar with diversity and trans- and interracial issues from the standpoint of an educator, but also from that of a <a class="zem_slink" title="Multiracial" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiracial">mixed-heritage</a> person—she describes herself as being of mixed Chinese and Belgian heritage. The I Am Malan Council hopes Van Kerckhove will readily add Malan to the list of elements that make-up her identity.</p>
<p>Frida Potente explains the decision to offer Van Kerckhove membership to the Malan race: &#8220;The work Carmen is doing to create a higher level of comfort in discussing issues of race is vital to getting us all to a point where we can move past the distraction of misconceptions and stereotypes, and really start getting closer to a place of empathy and humility.</p>
<p>Being candid about racial issues, creating an atmosphere where we are comfortable and unafraid to talk about what ails us—that&#8217;s the first step to revealing the underlying connections that exist between us.&#8221;</p>
<p>The Malan race is defined by ideology rather than by superficialities. Malans transcend racial stereotypes and the boundaries of archaic race categories. Malans form bonds based on linkages deeper than skin and, as a result, help move the world closer to racial unity, improved race relations, and toward the end of racism.</p>
<p>Membership to the Malan race is by invitation or award only, although invitations can be requested on the group&#8217;s site, <a href="http://www.iammalan.org/">http://www.iammalan.org</a>. <a class="zem_slink" title="Stephen Colbert" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Colbert">Stephen Colbert</a>, <a class="zem_slink" title="Michael Moore" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Moore">Michael Moore</a>, and John Oliver are recent Malan membership recipients.</p>
<p>Potente adds, &#8220;Carmen is a leader in the field and we are so pleased to extend membership to her. We are eager to learn from and grow with her.&#8221;</p>
<p>A popular blogger and podcaster, Van Kerckhove&#8217;s internet radio show, Addicted to Race, and her blog Love Isn&#8217;t Enough: On Raising a Family in a Colorstruck World, have lead to her being cited on NPR, <a class="zem_slink" title="USA Today" rel="homepage" href="http://www.usatoday.com/">USA Today</a>, and <a class="zem_slink" title="New York Times" rel="homepage" href="http://www.newyorktimes.com">The New York Times</a>.</p>
<p>As part of the welcome process, Van Kerckhove will receive an official Malan race certificate, as well as a short guide detailing how to live in the world as a Malan, and how to educate others on her new racial identity. An expanded FAQ—a condensed version of which is available on <a href="http://www.iammalan.org/">http://www.iammalan.org</a> -will also be provided.</p>
