		<item>
		<title>Michael Moore No Longer Afraid of Himself: Moore’s Membership to Malan Race Confirmed</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/ColorBlindPodshout/~3/YsmXVfLiWWw/</link>
		<comments>http://iammalan.org/wordpress/?p=32#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Dec 2009 19:31:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>contactthemalan@gmail.com (Frida Potente)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Malan News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[award]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[malan]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[membership]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[michael moore]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[race]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[racial identity]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://iammalan.org/wordpress/?p=32</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Moore gets some relief from his fear of white people since gaining membership to the Malan race. Also receives first posthumously awarded membership for former friend, Ray Simon.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="zemanta-img" style="display: block; width: 110px; margin: 1em;">
<div class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 110px"><br />
<a href="http://www.associatedcontent.com/article/2539659/michael_moore_no_longer_afraid_of_himself.html?cat=48"><img class="  " title="TOKYO - NOVEMBER 30:  Director Michael Moore a..." src="http://cache.daylife.com/imageserve/08jR9zv9AE7Tb/100x150.jpg" alt="TOKYO - NOVEMBER 30:  Director Michael Moore a..." width="100" height="150" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Image by Getty Images via Daylife</p></div>
</div>
<p>“White people scare the crap out of me,” <a class="zem_slink" title="Michael Moore" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Moore">Michael Moore</a> famously wrote in his 2001 book, <em><a class="zem_slink" title="Stupid White Men" rel="amazon" href="http://www.amazon.com/Stupid-White-Men-Micheal-Moore/dp/B000LMT67U%3FSubscriptionId%3D0G81C5DAZ03ZR9WH9X82%26tag%3Dzemanta-20%26linkCode%3Dxm2%26camp%3D2025%26creative%3D165953%26creativeASIN%3DB000LMT67U">Stupid White Men</a></em><em> &#8230;and Other Excuses for the State of the Nation! </em>Now a new member of the Malan race, at least Moore can no longer be afraid of himself.</p>
<p>Equally loved and not-so-loved—depending on the side of the fence one perches on—for his in-your-face, never back down, take-a-long-hard-and-extreme-close-up-look-at-this-mess approach to filmmaking, Moore and his films <em><a class="zem_slink" title="Roger &amp; Me [Region 2]" rel="amazon" href="http://www.amazon.com/Roger-Me-Region-Michael-Moore/dp/B00013KCLS%3FSubscriptionId%3D0G81C5DAZ03ZR9WH9X82%26tag%3Dzemanta-20%26linkCode%3Dxm2%26camp%3D2025%26creative%3D165953%26creativeASIN%3DB00013KCLS">Roger &amp; Me</a></em>, <em><a class="zem_slink" title="Fahrenheit 9/11" rel="amazon" href="http://www.amazon.com/Fahrenheit-9-11-Michael-Moore/dp/B000SINT52%3FSubscriptionId%3D0G81C5DAZ03ZR9WH9X82%26tag%3Dzemanta-20%26linkCode%3Dxm2%26camp%3D2025%26creative%3D165953%26creativeASIN%3DB000SINT52">Fahrenheit 9/11</a></em>, <em><a class="zem_slink" title="Sicko (Special Edition)" rel="amazon" href="http://www.amazon.com/Sicko-Special-Michael-Moore/dp/B000UNYJXQ%3FSubscriptionId%3D0G81C5DAZ03ZR9WH9X82%26tag%3Dzemanta-20%26linkCode%3Dxm2%26camp%3D2025%26creative%3D165953%26creativeASIN%3DB000UNYJXQ">Sicko</a></em>, and <em>Capitalism: A Love Story</em>, among others, have garnered him a large audience of supporters and a slew of awards, including a 2002 <a class="zem_slink" title="Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Documentary_Feature">Academy Award for Documentary Feature</a> for his gun violence exposé, <em><a class="zem_slink" title="Bowling for Columbine [Region 2]" rel="amazon" href="http://www.amazon.com/Bowling-Columbine-Region-Michael-Moore/dp/B0000916TJ%3FSubscriptionId%3D0G81C5DAZ03ZR9WH9X82%26tag%3Dzemanta-20%26linkCode%3Dxm2%26camp%3D2025%26creative%3D165953%26creativeASIN%3DB0000916TJ">Bowling for Columbine</a></em>.</p>
<p>Although Moore’s stance on issues such as American culture, and domestic and international policy is sometimes met with chilliness from those not leaning in his particularly liberal direction—such as at his Oscar acceptance speech where he blasted then <a class="zem_slink" title="George W. Bush" rel="homepage" href="http://www.georgewbushlibrary.gov">President George W. Bush</a> and was greeted by “loud boos from the audience of 3,500”—it is his gumption and courage to speak his discoveries and insights that earned him a place amongst the people of the Malan race. Moore joins fellow Malans Stephen Colbert and John Oliver who have both been recently adopted into the fledgling race.</p>
<p>“Part of being Malan is being able to nurture and empower the people around you,” says Frida Potente, President of the I Am Malan Council, “Michael does this with his films and books. He knows how to get things done in the world, how to convey a powerful message that incites in viewers and readers a new understanding of the issues and, in many, a desire to affect change. Michael is a mentor and we look forward to learning from and growing with him.”</p>
<p>Potente says that Malans are not bonded as a group by external appearances as are almost all other races. Instead, Malans identify as a <a class="zem_slink" title="Race (classification of human beings)" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Race_%28classification_of_human_beings%29">racial group</a> by their ideology rather than by, what the group refers to as, external superficialities.</p>
<p>Moore will also be presented with a posthumously awarded Malan race membership certificate for his one-time friend, Ray Simon. Simon was a marketing consultant and author, and used his talents to help Moore with the development of his website in the early part of the decade. Simon succumbed to cancer in 2002.</p>
<p>Simon published <em>Mischief Marketing</em>, which offers at once guerilla-style yet light-hearted advice on marketing to those with miniscule promotion budgets. He advocated innovation, creativity, and even undertaking gray area, borderline-legal but always safe and at least minimally-sane marketing strategies.</p>
<p>Simon wrote, “When you are on the verge of doing something important but difficult, people around you will often fail to recognize or appreciate what you’re doing.”</p>
<p>Simon, Moore would likely agree, would have appreciated being inducted into the Malan race.</p>
<p>As part of the welcome process, Moore will receive official Malan race certificates for both himself and Simon, as well as a short guide detailing how to live in the world as a Malan, and how to educate others on his new racial identity. An expanded FAQ&#8211; a condensed version of which is available on <a href="http://www.iammalan.org/" target="_blank">http://www.iammalan.org</a>&#8211;will also be provided to Moore.</p>
